					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    How to play a rogue</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Karmagaden Blackrose</a> | 
		            1/26/2001 7:03:53 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Rogues are a tank assist.  They are NOT tanks they need a tank to take the damage while they BS.  The following is some strategies on how to play a rogue.  Remember rogues are the &quot;weakest&quot; class when it comes to fighting!  We have all these cool abilities to make up for it.  Because of this playing a rogue is not about how much damage you do or what you armor class is because they will always be inferior at the same level.  Rather playing a rogue takes intelligence and deception.<BR>
<BR>
On PvP verse players.<BR>
A Rogue should NEVER EVER EVER EVER EVER EVER EVER.........EVER go against a FH Player on PvP.  Why?  Because quite simply we can give out and receive less damage than other classes.  The rogue primary ability is to AVOID combat.  This means you should smack the fools that are already damaged.  Stay invisible and watch a fight.  When the winner bends down to sack the losers corpse BANG nail him with a BS.  He will stand up and be confused for a sec.  Even better their mana and health will be low while you are at full.  Then strafe a lot!  Creatures will turn to face you when you strafe players have slower reactions and you can get more BS's in.  If you are attacker ignore the pet it will die with the caster.  Use your double attack and duel wield to interrupt the casters casting.  If they can't get a spell off they are toast.  Casters will then have a wonderful tendency to run away trying to get more space to cast spell.  Against creatures this works fine.  The creature will go after the pet.  With a rogue all this does is give a chance for some more BS's.  With a warrior they will just stand and take it, there is nothing else they can do.  A warrior MUST be at very low health for you to take him.  Use your spin and BS a lot you need it.  When you win there is no need to loot at first.  Hide immediately then use sneak to be sure you were unobserved.  If someone is running to kill you abandon the corpse and go.  If not loot your ill-gotten gains.<BR>
<BR>
Soloing against Creatures<BR>
DO NOT SOLO AGAINST CREATURES!<BR>
You may win one or two but you will not get the XP to balance all the times you have died.  If you are forced into combat then run to the closest zone DO NOT WAIT!  If you are against a caster there is one trick you can use.  When creatures cast they do not turn.  You can spin around them and nail them with a BS.  Even with this do not take them.<BR>
<BR>
In a group<BR>
YESS!!! The place for rogues!  In a group you can use all those special skills you have!  You know the ones that you gave up HP and attack rolls for.  What should you do in the group?  Well the basic job of the rogue like the monk is a puller.  Unlike a monk however we as rogues cannot feign death to drop the nasty mob on our tail.  There for we must be very sure of what we are pulling BEFORE we pull it.  Use sneak and hide to look at all the creatures in the area and see which ones will be pulled.  Then think back on your route in and think of all the creatures are there that will come.  If possible get a sow for this so that you will not be stunned and rooted or something like that.  When you get back to your party to not stop in front run past the party so that all the badies will go for someone else.  Then slip around behind the mob and begin to BS.  IT is importuned however to remember that your BS acts like a taunt.  Creatures will come after it.  Pick a warrior in your party.  Then assist him or her.  The warrior will be doing so much damage that no taunt will get the creature off.  After the first pull you should make sure that no one attacks you.  Not only does this mean that you are ready to pull again almost immediately if you all have to run for it you will still be fast enough to escape while the mob is chewing the rest of your party up.  If stuff does lock onto you use your cool antitaunt.  You can click attack off then hit hide.  If it works, and it sometimes does not, the badies will start to attack someone else.  NOTE: this only works when you are in a group.  Anti taunt makes the monster go to the next target.  This is worth less if you are the only target.  On the other abilities rogues are the scouts as a group moves though a dungeon.  Pick locks is useful in befallen and Velonious.  To use pick locks you need to have a lock pick set.  You can get them at the guild.  You then take the pick set and click it on the door.  Do not bother to set pick locks as a hot key it does nothing.  I have heard that find remove traps is very valuable in Velonius but I do not have any Xp with that yet so I cannot help you there.  Make and apply poison is good if you know you are going against a hard creature so it take forethought.  Instill doubt is almost useless.  It only works maybe&#8230;1/50 times?  This means that you can never know when it is going to work.  Best bet is to just keep clicking on it throughout the entire fight and hope it works<BR>
<BR>
In final, Remember you must think to be a rogue this is not a hack and slash or burn and boom class.  As of such it does not matter what race you are or what points you put into your stats.  The rogue class is hard to play but it is very rewarding.  <BR>
<BR>
P.S Be sure to work on bind wounds it is a common skill but useful when there is not cleric.<BR>
<BR>
Karmagaden Blackrose<BR>
26 Rogue<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
