			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				actually, they often dish out more damage than monks.<BR>
<BR>
here's some more advice.  if you can't get a group, partner up with a druid.  have them start off with a snare and a dot.  that'll really piss off the MOB and make it go after them.  then you just run along behind it, getting free jabs in and backstabs.  if it aggros on you, just back off it and let him root it.  then sit down and let the druid add another dot (dot really piss off MOBs, and so do roots).  med and sit till root breaks and it'll go back after the druid.  follow behind.  rinse and repeat.  make sure the druid keeps you sowed.  druid can also heal you if things get ugly and give you a strength buff.<BR>
<BR>
high str and high weapon damage are the prime factors in your backstabs.  a 6 damage piercer will do about half the backstab that a 9 damage piercer will do, so at low levels, try and get you hands on a bloodstaind fang (sell for real cheap and are 9/32).  also, focus on str gear.  things like jagged bands. +str earrings...etc.
				</font>
			</td>

